-- Veolia Awarded Water Supply Contract by Senart Val de Seine
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-06-13T11:50:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-13/veolia-awarded-water-supply-contract-by-senart-val-de-seine.html
Veolia Environnement (VIE) , Europe’s
largest water company, was awarded a water-supply network
management contract valued at 20 million euros ($27 million) by
the Senart Val de Seine urban authority.  The contract to manage Draveil’s water network allows
Veolia Water to establish operations in a new area of the
Essonne department, part of the Ile-de-France region surrounding
Paris, the company said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
